parameters.toolDescription:
Create a dataset snapshot based on a provided filter in BrightData. use always filter homeStatus = FOR_SALE. We have the next operators: =, >, >=, in, <, <=, not_array_includes, !=, not_in, not_includes

Filter must follow the next format:
{
    "operator": "and",
    "filters": [
        {
            "name": "homeStatus",
            "operator": "=",
            "value": "FOR_SALE"
        },
        {
            "name": "price",
            "operator": "=",
            "value": 1000000
        },
        {
            "name": "city",
            "operator": "=",
            "value": "new york"
        },
        {
            "name": "bathrooms",
            "operator": "=",
            "value": 2
        },
        {
            "name": "bedrooms",
            "operator": "=",
            "value": 4
        }
    ]
}
